title: Commission Regulation (EEC) No 1165/92 of 5 May 1992 re- establishing the levying of customs duties on products categories 1, 9 and 32 (order No 40.0010, 40.0090 and 40.0320), originating in Indonesia, to which the preferential tariff arrangements set out in Council Regulation (EEC) No 3832/90 apply
header:
COMMISSION REGULATION (EEC) No 1165/92  of 5 May 1992  re-establishing the levying of customs duties on products categories 1, 9 and 32 (order No 40.0010, 40.0090 and 40.0320), originating in Indonesia, to which the preferential tariff  arrangements set out in Council Regulation (EEC) No 3832/90 apply
THE COMMISSION OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES
main_body:
As from 10 May 1992 the levying of customs duties, suspended pursuant to Regulation (EEC) No 3832/90, shall be re-established in respect of the following products, imported into the Community and originating in Indonesia:

5802 30 00  Woven pile fabrics and chenille fabrics (other than terry towelling or terry fabrics of cotton and narrow woven fabrics) and tufted textile fabrics of wool, of cotton or of man-made textile fibres

This Regulation shall enter into force on the third day following its publication in the Official Journal of the European Communities. This Regulation shall be binding in its entirety and directly applicable in all Member States.
